olive oil
1 packet beef strips
1 packet garlic paste
1 packet Honey-Soy Sauce
1 packet Microwavable Basmati Rice
1 packet roasted peanuts
1 cucumber
1 packet garlic aioli
1 packet ponzu sauce
1 packet Crispy Shallots
1 bag coriander
1 bag Asian Slaw Mix

• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over high heat
• Cook beef strips in batches until browned, 1 min
• Return all beef to the pan, then add garlic paste and honey-soy sauce and cook until slightly reduced and fragrant, 1 min. Set aside

• Microwave rice until steaming, 2-3 mins
• Crush roasted peanuts in their packet. Add peanuts and rice to a bowl. Season and stir to combine

• Roughly chop cucumber
• In a bowl, combine cucumber, slaw mix and ponzu sauce. Season
• Plate up rice, slaw and beef
• Serve with garlic aioli and crispy shallots. Garnish with torn coriander to serve